              <div id=\"content\">\n<form id=\"j_id0:j_id1:j_id103\" name=\"j_id0:j_id1:j_id103\" method=\"post\" action=\"/ShPo_HomePage\" enctype=\"application/x-www-form-urlencoded\">\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"j_id0:j_id1:j_id103\" value=\"j_id0:j_id1:j_id103\">\n\n         <section class=\"supportingtext\"><span id=\"j_id0:j_id1:j_id103:optabs\">\n                <div class=\"hometabs\" id=\"mainContent\">\n                    \n                    <ul class=\"nav nav-tabs\">\n                        <li class=\"active\"><a data-toggle=\"tab\" href=\"#AboutTheRegister\">About the Register</a></li>\n                        <li><a data-toggle=\"tab\" href=\"#WhoFCARegulatesTabPane\">About the FCA/ PRA</a></li>\n                        \n                        <li><a data-toggle=\"tab\" href=\"#FinancialsScamsTabPane\">Beware of financial scams</a></li>\n                    </ul>\n                    \n                    <div class=\"tab-content\">\n                        <div class=\"tab-pane fade in active\" id=\"AboutTheRegister\"><p>The Financial Services Register is a public record that shows details of firms, individuals and other bodies that are, or have been, regulated by the  <a href=\"http://www.bankofengland.co.uk/pra/Pages/default.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Prudential Regulation Authority (PRA)</a> and/or the <a href=\"http://www.fca.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Financial Conduct Authority (FCA)</a>.  It also has information on firms regulated by the Financial Services Authority that had cancelled or stopped being regulated before April 2013.</p>\n<p><strong>Why search the Register?</strong><br>\nYou can search the Register to find out whether a firm you are using, or plan to do business with, is&nbsp;<span class=\"search_popover\" data-toggle=\"popover\" data-placement=\"top\" data-content=\"<div class='searchPopover'>A firm that is given permission to provide regulated products and services.</div>\" data-original-title=\"\" title=\"\">authorised</span>&nbsp;or&nbsp;registered&nbsp;by the PRA and/or FCA, or is exempt. You can also see if a consumer credit firm has interim permission to provide consumer credit.</p><p> \nOther information you can see about a firm or individual includes:</p> \n<ul> \n<li>the main contact details, trading names and other basic information </li> \n<li>the 'status' of a firm or individual, e.g. whether they are authorised or approved</li> \n<li>the name and basic details of some firms and individuals that are providing products or services in the UK or abroad without the required authorisation, approval or exemption from regulation</li> \n<li>Under the new Senior Managers and Certification Regime, effective from 7 March 2016, which covers banks, building societies, credit unions and PRA designated investment firms, only Senior Managers are pre-approved. Firms  now assess other functions such as Customer Functions (CF30s) (including retail investment advisers). Individuals will show a current status of Inactive on the&nbsp;register in these firms if they used to be approved by the FCA.</li>\n<li>If an adviser is not listed, or shown as inactive, and you would like to check their status, you should confirm this directly with the firm the adviser is currently working with.</li> \n</ul>\n\n<p>If you deal with a firm (or individual) that is not regulated you may not be covered by the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.financial-ombudsman.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Financial Ombudsman Service</a>&nbsp;or <a href=\"http://www.fscs.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Financial Services Compensation Scheme</a>&nbsp;if things go wrong.</p><p>\n  You can also search the Register for individuals that work in an authorised firm and perform some important tasks that have been&nbsp;<span class=\"search_popover\" data-toggle=\"popover\" data-placement=\"top\" data-content=\"<div class='searchPopover'>An individual (and some firms) that can perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We describe these individuals and firms as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions.</div>\" data-original-title=\"\" title=\"\">&nbsp;approved&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;by the FCA or PRA.</p><p><strong>Other registers </strong><br>The <a href=\"https://mutuals.fsa.gov.uk/?\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Mutuals Register</a> is a public record of building societies, credit unions and other registered societies under the Co-operative and Community Benefit Societies Act 2014.</p><p>The <a href=\"https://www.fca.org.uk/firms/regulated-covered-bonds-register\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Regulated Covered Bonds Register</a> is a public record of all regulated covered bonds and their issuers. Covered bonds are a type of secured bond usually backed by mortgages or public sector loans.</p>\n                        </div>\n                        \n                        <div class=\"tab-pane fade\" id=\"WhoFCARegulatesTabPane\"><p>The FCA regulates and supervises the conduct of more than 50,000 firms in the UK that provide financial products and services to both UK and international customers.</p>\n<p>The PRA is responsible for the&nbsp;<span class=\"search_popover\" data-toggle=\"popover\" data-placement=\"top\" data-content=\"<div class='searchPopover'>Prudential regulation sets minimum standards that require firms to conduct business in a sound and prudent manner, avoid excessive risk-taking, manage risks and hold sufficient capital to protect the stability of the firm and UK financial system. </div>\" data-original-title=\"\" title=\"\">prudential regulation</span>&nbsp;and supervision of banks, building societies, credit unions, insurers and major investment firms.</p>\n<p>The FCA also regulates the prudential standards of firms not covered by the PRA.</p>\n<h2>Other organisations that can help</h2>\n<p><b>Companies</b> <a href=\"http://www.companieshouse.gov.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Companies House</a> has further information on companies in the UK, including some financial services firms.</p>\n<p><b>Complaints</b> The <a href=\"http://www.financial-ombudsman.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Financial Ombudsman Service</a> is the free, independent service in the UK for settling disputes between businesses that provide financial products and services, and their customers.</p><p>The <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/groups/claims-management-regulator\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Ministry of Justice</a> regulates companies that offer a service to claim compensation from a firm - you should contact it for complaints about claims handlers (also known as claims management companies).</p><p><b>Compensation</b> The <a href=\"http://www.fscs.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Financial Services Compensation Scheme (FSCS)</a> may be able to compensate certain eligible individuals (and some small businesses) that are, or were, customers of an&nbsp;<span class=\"search_popover\" data-toggle=\"popover\" data-placement=\"top\" data-content=\"<div class='searchPopover'>A firm that is given permission to provide regulated products and services.</div>\" data-original-title=\"\" title=\"\">authorised</span>&nbsp;firm that has been declared in default.</p>\n                        </div>\n                        \n                        \n                        \n                         \n                        <div class=\"tab-pane fade\" id=\"FinancialsScamsTabPane\"><p>Firms and individuals can only offer most financial products and services in the UK if they are&nbsp;<span class=\"search_popover\" data-toggle=\"popover\" data-placement=\"top\" data-content=\"<div class='searchPopover'>A firm that is given permission to provide regulated products and services.</div>\" data-original-title=\"\" title=\"\">authorised</span>, registered&nbsp;or approved to do so, or are otherwise exempt.</p>\n<p>Yet some act without our authorisation or registration, or without being exempt, and some knowingly run scams.</p><p>If you deal with a firm (or individual) that is not regulated you may not be covered by the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.financial-ombudsman.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Financial Ombudsman Service</a>&nbsp;or <a href=\"http://www.fscs.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Financial Services Compensation Scheme</a>&nbsp;if things go wrong. Search for a firm or individual to find out how you are protected.</p><p><b>Protect yourself from scams</b> Find out how to <a href=\"http://www.fca.org.uk/consumers/protect-yourself/unauthorised-firms\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">check you are dealing with a regulated firm</a>.</p><p>You can see <a href=\"http://www.fca.org.uk/consumers/scams/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">what to do if you have been scammed</a>, are concerned about an investment or have been contacted by fraudsters.</p><p>You can also help us protect other people if you <a href=\"http://www.fca.org.uk/consumers/protect-yourself/report-an-unauthorised-firm\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">report a scam or unauthorised firm.</a></p>\n                        </div>\n                        \n                    </div>\n                    \n                </div></span>\n            \n  \n                                },\n                            },\n                            \n                            debug: true\n                        });\n                    });\n                    </script>\n                 </div>\n            </div>\n             \n            \n            \n            <div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"myModalLabel\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"typeofbusinessmodal\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n              <div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n                <div class=\"modal-content\">\n                  <div class=\"modal-header\">\n                    <button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"close\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\"></span></button>\n                    <h3 class=\"modal-title\" id=\"myModalLabel\">Type of business</h3>\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-body\"><p><strong>Financial services firm</strong> - Firms must be authorised to provide regulated products and services, including banking, investments, insurance, mortgages and other financial products and services in the UK. </p><p><strong>Individual</strong> - Individuals (and some firms) must be approved to perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We describe these as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions. </p><p><strong>Payment services firm</strong> - Firms must be authorised or registered to provide payment services, including issuing credit cards and  money transfer operations.</p><p><strong>Consumer Credit Interim</strong> - A consumer credit firm that held an Office of Fair Trading licence and wanted to continue its consumer credit activities had to apply for interim permission. This will last until it has to apply for authorisation or a variation of permission.</p><p><strong>EMoney</strong> - Firms must be authorised or registered to issue electronic money (e-money), which includes pre-paid cards such as travel money cards and some gift cards.</p> <p><strong>Unauthorised firm</strong> - Some firms provide products and services without the required authorisation, or is knowingly running a scam. We strongly suggest you avoid dealing with unauthorised firms.</p><p><strong>Collective investment scheme</strong> - Some collective investment schemes (CIS) are regulated by us, including investment companies with variable capital (open ended investment companies), some unit trusts, and recognised offshore schemes.</p><p><strong>Exempt professional firm</strong> - Some firms (such as solicitors, accountants and chartered surveyors) can perform limited regulated financial activities as part of their normal professional services, without being authorised or an agent of an authorised firm.</p><p><strong>Exchange</strong> - We recognise and supervise certain investment exchanges.</p><p><strong>Not-for-profit body</strong> - Not-for-profit bodies may be covered by a group licence to provide financial services, debt management services and credit information services.</p>&nbsp;\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-footer\">\n                    <button class=\"btn btn-default modalbtn\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\">Close</button>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n           \n            \n            <div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"myModalLabel\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"currentstatusmodal\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n              <div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n                <div class=\"modal-content\">\n                  <div class=\"modal-header\">\n                    <button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"close\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\"></span></button>\n                    <h3 class=\"modal-title\" id=\"myModalLabel\">Current status</h3>\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-body\"><p><strong>Active Individual</strong> - An individual (and some firms) that can perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We describe these individuals and firms as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions.</p> <p><strong>Appointed representative</strong> - A firm or individual that can act on behalf of another firm (its principal) that is authorised in the UK or regulated in another EEA country. The principal is responsible for the appointed representative's activities.</p> <p><strong>Appointed representative  former</strong> - An appointed representative that can no longer provide regulated products and services, but previously could act on behalf of another firm (its principal).</p> <p><strong>Appointed representative  introducer</strong> - A firm that can introduce customers to another firm or members of the firms group, and/or give out certain kinds of marketing material. It must be a representative of a firm authorised by the FCA or PRA, or regulated in the EEA.</p> <p><strong>Approved</strong> - An individual (and some firms) that can perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We describe these individuals and firms as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions.</p><p><strong>Authorised firm</strong> - A firm that is given permission to provide regulated products and services.</p> <p><strong>Authorised firm  applied to cancel</strong> - A firm that has applied to cancel its authorisation but must still meet our standards in dealing with its customers.</p> <p><strong>Authorised firm  in administration</strong> - A firm that has stopped taking on new business but is still authorised and has to continue to meet our standards in dealing with its customers.</p> <p><strong>Authorised firm  in liquidation</strong> - A firm that has stopped taking on new business but is still authorised and has to continue to meet our standards in dealing with its customers.</p> <p><strong>Authorised firm  suspended</strong> - A firm that has to stop providing regulated products and services for a period of time.</p> <p><strong>Authorised electronic money institution</strong> - A firm that we have given permission to issue electronic money (e-money) and provide payment services.</p><p><strong>Authorised payment institution</strong> - A firm that we have given permission to provide payment services.</p> <p><strong>EEA authorised firm</strong> - A firm regulated in another <span class=\"search_popover\" data-toggle=\"popover\" data-placement=\"top\" data-content=\"<div class='searchPopover'> The EEA includes the EU states, plus Iceland, Norway and Liechtenstein.</div>\" data-original-title=\"\" title=\"\">European Economic Area</span> a (EEA) country that can offer certain products or services in the UK. The firm must meet minimum standards agreed across all EEA countries.</p><p><strong>Electronic money agent</strong> - A firm that can issue electronic money (e-money) and provide payment services on behalf of an e-money institution.</p><p><strong>Inactive individual</strong> - An individual (and some firms) that was previously approved to perform certain tasks in a regulated firm. These individuals and firms would have been described as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions. </p><p><strong>No longer authorised firm</strong> - A firm that can no longer provide regulated products and services, but previously was authorised by the PRA and/or FCA. </p><p><strong>Payment services agent</strong> - A firm that can provide payment services on behalf of a payment institution.</p><p><strong>Small electronic money institution</strong> - A firm that can issue electronic money (e-money) and provide payment services. These firms are registered (rather than authorised), which affects how we regulate the firm. </p><p><strong>Small payment institution</strong> - A firm that can provide payment services. These firms are registered (rather than authorised), which affects how we regulate the firm. </p> <p><strong>Unauthorised firm</strong> - Some firms provide products and services without the required authorisation, or is knowingly running a scam. We strongly suggest you avoid dealing with unauthorised firms.</p> <p><strong>No longer Authorised</strong> - This is a firm that can no longer provide regulated products and services, but was previously authorised by the PRA and/or FCA.</p> <p><strong>Cancelled</strong> - The firm has cancelled its interim permission to undertake consumer credit business.</p> <p><strong>Previously IP Registered</strong> - This firm previously had interim permission to perform certain consumer credit activities for the period indicated in this record.  It has since applied for and been authorised to carry out credit activities in its main permission, replacing the interim permission. You should refer to the authorisation record for this firm for the permissions since the interim permission ended.</p> <p><strong>Fully Authorised apart from 2nd charge</strong> - This firm is authorised to run consumer credit business. You should refer to the authorisation information for this firm rather than its interim permission, except for its second charge mortgage business which still comes under its interim permission.</p> <p><strong>Interim Permission Granted</strong> - The firm has interim permission to undertake consumer credit business.</p> <p><strong>IP issued</strong> - The firm has interim permission to undertake consumer credit business.</p> <p><strong>IP provisionally issued</strong> - The firm has interim permission to undertake consumer credit business.</p> <p><strong>IVOP issued</strong> - This firm has interim permission to run consumer credit business and was already authorised to provide financial products and services.</p> <p><strong>IVOP provisionally granted</strong> - The firm has interim permission to undertake consumer credit business and was already authorised to provide financial products and services.</p> <p><strong>Lapsed</strong> - The firm no longer has interim permission to undertake consumer credit business.</p> <p><strong>Revoked</strong> - This firm has had its interim permission to run consumer credit business withdrawn. See the disciplinary and regulatory action section for more information.</p> <p><strong>Suspended</strong> - This firm has had its interim permission to undertake consumer credit business suspended by the FCA and/or PRA. See the Disciplinary and regulatory action about the firm for further information.</p> &nbsp;\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-footer\">\n                    <button class=\"btn btn-default modalbtn\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\">Close</button>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n            \n            \n            \n             \n            <div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"myModalLabel\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"AdvSrchtypeofbusinessmodal\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n              <div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n                <div class=\"modal-content\">\n                  <div class=\"modal-header\">\n                    <button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"close\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\"></span></button>\n                    <h3 class=\"modal-title\" id=\"myModalLabel\">Type of business</h3>\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-body\"><p><strong>Financial services firm</strong> - Firms must be authorised to provide regulated products and services, including banking, investments, insurance, mortgages and other financial products and services in the UK. </p><p><strong>Individual</strong> - Individuals (and some firms) must be approved to perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We strongly suggest you avoid dealing with unauthorised firms.</p><p><strong>Active Individual</strong> - An individual (and some firms) that can perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We describe these individuals and firms as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions.</p> <p><strong>Authorised CIS</strong> - This is a fund set up in the UK that is available for investment.</p><p><strong>Recognised CIS</strong> - This is a fund set up in another country that can be marketed to investors in the UK and is available for investment.</p><p><strong>De-recognised CIS</strong> - This is a fund set up in another country that can no longer be marketed to investors in the UK.</p>   &nbsp;\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-footer\">\n                    <button class=\"btn btn-default modalbtn\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\">Close</button>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n            \n            \n          \n    <span id=\"j_id0:j_id179\">\n\n<style>\n    .tls_warning_container_hidden { display: none;  \n                                },\n                            },\n                            \n                            debug: true\n                        });\n                    });\n                    </script>\n                 </div>\n            </div>\n             \n            \n            \n            <div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"myModalLabel\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"typeofbusinessmodal\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n              <div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n                <div class=\"modal-content\">\n                  <div class=\"modal-header\">\n                    <button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"close\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\"></span></button>\n                    <h3 class=\"modal-title\" id=\"myModalLabel\">Type of business</h3>\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-body\"><p><strong>Financial services firm</strong> - Firms must be authorised to provide regulated products and services, including banking, investments, insurance, mortgages and other financial products and services in the UK. </p><p><strong>Individual</strong> - Individuals (and some firms) must be approved to perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We describe these as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions. </p><p><strong>Payment services firm</strong> - Firms must be authorised or registered to provide payment services, including issuing credit cards and  money transfer operations.</p><p><strong>Consumer Credit Interim</strong> - A consumer credit firm that held an Office of Fair Trading licence and wanted to continue its consumer credit activities had to apply for interim permission. This will last until it has to apply for authorisation or a variation of permission.</p><p><strong>EMoney</strong> - Firms must be authorised or registered to issue electronic money (e-money), which includes pre-paid cards such as travel money cards and some gift cards.</p> <p><strong>Unauthorised firm</strong> - Some firms provide products and services without the required authorisation, or is knowingly running a scam. We strongly suggest you avoid dealing with unauthorised firms.</p><p><strong>Collective investment scheme</strong> - Some collective investment schemes (CIS) are regulated by us, including investment companies with variable capital (open ended investment companies), some unit trusts, and recognised offshore schemes.</p><p><strong>Exempt professional firm</strong> - Some firms (such as solicitors, accountants and chartered surveyors) can perform limited regulated financial activities as part of their normal professional services, without being authorised or an agent of an authorised firm.</p><p><strong>Exchange</strong> - We recognise and supervise certain investment exchanges.</p><p><strong>Not-for-profit body</strong> - Not-for-profit bodies may be covered by a group licence to provide financial services, debt management services and credit information services.</p>&nbsp;\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-footer\">\n                    <button class=\"btn btn-default modalbtn\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\">Close</button>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n           \n            \n            <div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"myModalLabel\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"currentstatusmodal\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n              <div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n                <div class=\"modal-content\">\n                  <div class=\"modal-header\">\n                    <button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"close\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\"></span></button>\n                    <h3 class=\"modal-title\" id=\"myModalLabel\">Current status</h3>\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-body\"><p><strong>Active Individual</strong> - An individual (and some firms) that can perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We describe these individuals and firms as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions.</p> <p><strong>Appointed representative</strong> - A firm or individual that can act on behalf of another firm (its principal) that is authorised in the UK or regulated in another EEA country. The principal is responsible for the appointed representative's activities.</p> <p><strong>Appointed representative  former</strong> - An appointed representative that can no longer provide regulated products and services, but previously could act on behalf of another firm (its principal).</p> <p><strong>Appointed representative  introducer</strong> - A firm that can introduce customers to another firm or members of the firms group, and/or give out certain kinds of marketing material. It must be a representative of a firm authorised by the FCA or PRA, or regulated in the EEA.</p> <p><strong>Approved</strong> - An individual (and some firms) that can perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We describe these individuals and firms as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions.</p><p><strong>Authorised firm</strong> - A firm that is given permission to provide regulated products and services.</p> <p><strong>Authorised firm  applied to cancel</strong> - A firm that has applied to cancel its authorisation but must still meet our standards in dealing with its customers.</p> <p><strong>Authorised firm  in administration</strong> - A firm that has stopped taking on new business but is still authorised and has to continue to meet our standards in dealing with its customers.</p> <p><strong>Authorised firm  in liquidation</strong> - A firm that has stopped taking on new business but is still authorised and has to continue to meet our standards in dealing with its customers.</p> <p><strong>Authorised firm  suspended</strong> - A firm that has to stop providing regulated products and services for a period of time.</p> <p><strong>Authorised electronic money institution</strong> - A firm that we have given permission to issue electronic money (e-money) and provide payment services.</p><p><strong>Authorised payment institution</strong> - A firm that we have given permission to provide payment services.</p> <p><strong>EEA authorised firm</strong> - A firm regulated in another <span class=\"search_popover\" data-toggle=\"popover\" data-placement=\"top\" data-content=\"<div class='searchPopover'> The EEA includes the EU states, plus Iceland, Norway and Liechtenstein.</div>\" data-original-title=\"\" title=\"\">European Economic Area</span> a (EEA) country that can offer certain products or services in the UK. The firm must meet minimum standards agreed across all EEA countries.</p><p><strong>Electronic money agent</strong> - A firm that can issue electronic money (e-money) and provide payment services on behalf of an e-money institution.</p><p><strong>Inactive individual</strong> - An individual (and some firms) that was previously approved to perform certain tasks in a regulated firm. These individuals and firms would have been described as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions. </p><p><strong>No longer authorised firm</strong> - A firm that can no longer provide regulated products and services, but previously was authorised by the PRA and/or FCA. </p><p><strong>Payment services agent</strong> - A firm that can provide payment services on behalf of a payment institution.</p><p><strong>Small electronic money institution</strong> - A firm that can issue electronic money (e-money) and provide payment services. These firms are registered (rather than authorised), which affects how we regulate the firm. </p><p><strong>Small payment institution</strong> - A firm that can provide payment services. These firms are registered (rather than authorised), which affects how we regulate the firm. </p> <p><strong>Unauthorised firm</strong> - Some firms provide products and services without the required authorisation, or is knowingly running a scam. We strongly suggest you avoid dealing with unauthorised firms.</p> <p><strong>No longer Authorised</strong> - This is a firm that can no longer provide regulated products and services, but was previously authorised by the PRA and/or FCA.</p> <p><strong>Cancelled</strong> - The firm has cancelled its interim permission to undertake consumer credit business.</p> <p><strong>Previously IP Registered</strong> - This firm previously had interim permission to perform certain consumer credit activities for the period indicated in this record.  It has since applied for and been authorised to carry out credit activities in its main permission, replacing the interim permission. You should refer to the authorisation record for this firm for the permissions since the interim permission ended.</p> <p><strong>Fully Authorised apart from 2nd charge</strong> - This firm is authorised to run consumer credit business. You should refer to the authorisation information for this firm rather than its interim permission, except for its second charge mortgage business which still comes under its interim permission.</p> <p><strong>Interim Permission Granted</strong> - The firm has interim permission to undertake consumer credit business.</p> <p><strong>IP issued</strong> - The firm has interim permission to undertake consumer credit business.</p> <p><strong>IP provisionally issued</strong> - The firm has interim permission to undertake consumer credit business.</p> <p><strong>IVOP issued</strong> - This firm has interim permission to run consumer credit business and was already authorised to provide financial products and services.</p> <p><strong>IVOP provisionally granted</strong> - The firm has interim permission to undertake consumer credit business and was already authorised to provide financial products and services.</p> <p><strong>Lapsed</strong> - The firm no longer has interim permission to undertake consumer credit business.</p> <p><strong>Revoked</strong> - This firm has had its interim permission to run consumer credit business withdrawn. See the disciplinary and regulatory action section for more information.</p> <p><strong>Suspended</strong> - This firm has had its interim permission to undertake consumer credit business suspended by the FCA and/or PRA. See the Disciplinary and regulatory action about the firm for further information.</p> &nbsp;\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-footer\">\n                    <button class=\"btn btn-default modalbtn\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\">Close</button>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n            \n            \n            \n             \n            <div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"myModalLabel\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"AdvSrchtypeofbusinessmodal\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n              <div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n                <div class=\"modal-content\">\n                  <div class=\"modal-header\">\n                    <button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"close\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\"></span></button>\n                    <h3 class=\"modal-title\" id=\"myModalLabel\">Type of business</h3>\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-body\"><p><strong>Financial services firm</strong> - Firms must be authorised to provide regulated products and services, including banking, investments, insurance, mortgages and other financial products and services in the UK. </p><p><strong>Individual</strong> - Individuals (and some firms) must be approved to perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We describe these as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions. </p><p><strong>Collective investment scheme</strong> - Some collective investment schemes (CIS) are regulated by us, including investment companies with variable capital (open ended investment companies), some unit trusts, and recognised offshore schemes.</p>&nbsp;\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-footer\">\n                    <button class=\"btn btn-default modalbtn\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\">Close</button>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n           \n            \n            <div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"myModalLabel\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"AdvSrchcurrentstatusmodal\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n              <div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n                <div class=\"modal-content\">\n                  <div class=\"modal-header\">\n                    <button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"close\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\"></span></button>\n                    <h3 class=\"modal-title\" id=\"myModalLabel\">Current status</h3>\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-body\"><p><strong>Authorised firm</strong> - A firm that is given permission to provide regulated products and services.</p><p><strong>Unauthorised firm</strong> - Some firms provide products and services without the required authorisation, or is knowingly running a scam. We strongly suggest you avoid dealing with unauthorised firms.</p><p><strong>Active Individual</strong> - An individual (and some firms) that can perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We describe these individuals and firms as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions.</p> <p><strong>Authorised CIS</strong> - This is a fund set up in the UK that is available for investment.</p><p><strong>Recognised CIS</strong> - This is a fund set up in another country that can be marketed to investors in the UK and is available for investment.</p><p><strong>De-recognised CIS</strong> - This is a fund set up in another country that can no longer be marketed to investors in the UK.</p>   &nbsp;\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-footer\">\n                    <button class=\"btn btn-default modalbtn\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\">Close</button>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n            \n            \n          \n    <script type=\"text/javascript\">Sfdc.onReady(function(){\n\tSfdcApp && SfdcApp.Visualforce && SfdcApp.Visualforce.VSManager && SfdcApp.Visualforce.VSManager.vfPrepareForms([\"j_id0:j_id1:j_id110\",\"j_id0:j_id1:j_id40:j_id41:registersearch:j_id43\"]);\n\n});</script></body>"}

class=\"pull-right visible-xs\">\n                            <button class=\"btn btn-primary btn-xs\" data-toggle=\"offcanvas\" type=\"button\">Tools</button>\n                        </p>\n                        <div id=\"content\">\n<form id=\"j_id0:j_id1:j_id103\" name=\"j_id0:j_id1:j_id103\" method=\"post\" action=\"/ShPo_HomePage\" enctype=\"application/x-www-form-urlencoded\">\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"j_id0:j_id1:j_id103\" value=\"j_id0:j_id1:j_id103\">\n\n         <section class=\"supportingtext\"><span id=\"j_id0:j_id1:j_id103:optabs\">\n                <div class=\"hometabs\" id=\"mainContent\">\n                    \n                    <ul class=\"nav nav-tabs\">\n                        <li class=\"active\"><a data-toggle=\"tab\" href=\"#AboutTheRegister\">About the Register</a></li>\n                        <li><a data-toggle=\"tab\" href=\"#WhoFCARegulatesTabPane\">About the FCA/ PRA</a></li>\n                        \n                        <li><a data-toggle=\"tab\" href=\"#FinancialsScamsTabPane\">Beware of financial scams</a></li>\n                    </ul>\n                    \n                    <div class=\"tab-content\">\n                        <div class=\"tab-pane fade in active\" id=\"AboutTheRegister\"><p>The Financial Services Register is a public record that shows details of firms, individuals and other bodies that are, or have been, regulated by the  <a href=\"http://www.bankofengland.co.uk/pra/Pages/default.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Prudential Regulation Authority (PRA)</a> and/or the <a href=\"http://www.fca.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Financial Conduct Authority (FCA)</a>.  It also has information on firms regulated by the Financial Services Authority that had cancelled or stopped being regulated before April 2013.</p>\n<p><strong>Why search the Register?</strong><br>\nYou can search the Register to find out whether a firm you are using, or plan to do business with, is&nbsp;<span class=\"search_popover\" data-toggle=\"popover\" data-placement=\"top\" data-content=\"<div class='searchPopover'>A firm that is given permission to provide regulated products and services.</div>\" data-original-title=\"\" title=\"\">authorised</span>&nbsp;or&nbsp;registered&nbsp;by the PRA and/or FCA, or is exempt. You can also see if a consumer credit firm has interim permission to provide consumer credit.</p><p> \nOther information you can see about a firm or individual includes:</p> \n<ul> \n<li>the main contact details, trading names and other basic information </li> \n<li>the 'status' of a firm or individual, e.g. whether they are authorised or approved</li> \n<li>the name and basic details of some firms and individuals that are providing products or services in the UK or abroad without the required authorisation, approval or exemption from regulation</li> \n<li>Under the new Senior Managers and Certification Regime, effective from 7 March 2016, which covers banks, building societies, credit unions and PRA designated investment firms, only Senior Managers are pre-approved. Firms  now assess other functions such as Customer Functions (CF30s) (including retail investment advisers). Individuals will show a current status of Inactive on the&nbsp;register in these firms if they used to be approved by the FCA.</li>\n<li>If an adviser is not listed, or shown as inactive, and you would like to check their status, you should confirm this directly with the firm the adviser is currently working with.</li> \n</ul>\n\n<p>If you deal with a firm (or individual) that is not regulated you may not be covered by the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.financial-ombudsman.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Financial Ombudsman Service</a>&nbsp;or <a href=\"http://www.fscs.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Financial Services Compensation Scheme</a>&nbsp;if things go wrong.</p><p>\n  You can also search the Register for individuals that work in an authorised firm and perform some important tasks that have been&nbsp;<span class=\"search_popover\" data-toggle=\"popover\" data-placement=\"top\" data-content=\"<div class='searchPopover'>An individual (and some firms) that can perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We describe these individuals and firms as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions.</div>\" data-original-title=\"\" title=\"\">&nbsp;approved&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;by the FCA or PRA.</p><p><strong>Other registers </strong><br>The <a href=\"https://mutuals.fsa.gov.uk/?\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Mutuals Register</a> is a public record of building societies, credit unions and other registered societies under the Co-operative and Community Benefit Societies Act 2014.</p><p>The <a href=\"https://www.fca.org.uk/firms/regulated-covered-bonds-register\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Regulated Covered Bonds Register</a> is a public record of all regulated covered bonds and their issuers. Covered bonds are a type of secured bond usually backed by mortgages or public sector loans.</p>\n                        </div>\n                        \n                        <div class=\"tab-pane fade\" id=\"WhoFCARegulatesTabPane\"><p>The FCA regulates and supervises the conduct of more than 50,000 firms in the UK that provide financial products and services to both UK and international customers.</p>\n<p>The PRA is responsible for the&nbsp;<span class=\"search_popover\" data-toggle=\"popover\" data-placement=\"top\" data-content=\"<div class='searchPopover'>Prudential regulation sets minimum standards that require firms to conduct business in a sound and prudent manner, avoid excessive risk-taking, manage risks and hold sufficient capital to protect the stability of the firm and UK financial system. </div>\" data-original-title=\"\" title=\"\">prudential regulation</span>&nbsp;and supervision of banks, building societies, credit unions, insurers and major investment firms.</p>\n<p>The FCA also regulates the prudential standards of firms not covered by the PRA.</p>\n<h2>Other organisations that can help</h2>\n<p><b>Companies</b> <a href=\"http://www.companieshouse.gov.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Companies House</a> has further information on companies in the UK, including some financial services firms.</p>\n<p><b>Complaints</b> The <a href=\"http://www.financial-ombudsman.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Financial Ombudsman Service</a> is the free, independent service in the UK for settling disputes between businesses that provide financial products and services, and their customers.</p><p>The <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/groups/claims-management-regulator\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Ministry of Justice</a> regulates companies that offer a service to claim compensation from a firm - you should contact it for complaints about claims handlers (also known as claims management companies).</p><p><b>Compensation</b> The <a href=\"http://www.fscs.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Financial Services Compensation Scheme (FSCS)</a> may be able to compensate certain eligible individuals (and some small businesses) that are, or were, customers of an&nbsp;<span class=\"search_popover\" data-toggle=\"popover\" data-placement=\"top\" data-content=\"<div class='searchPopover'>A firm that is given permission to provide regulated products and services.</div>\" data-original-title=\"\" title=\"\">authorised</span>&nbsp;firm that has been declared in default.</p>\n                        </div>\n                        \n                        \n                        \n                         \n                        <div class=\"tab-pane fade\" id=\"FinancialsScamsTabPane\"><p>Firms and individuals can only offer most financial products and services in the UK if they are&nbsp;<span class=\"search_popover\" data-toggle=\"popover\" data-placement=\"top\" data-content=\"<div class='searchPopover'>A firm that is given permission to provide regulated products and services.</div>\" data-original-title=\"\" title=\"\">authorised</span>, registered&nbsp;or approved to do so, or are otherwise exempt.</p>\n<p>Yet some act without our authorisation or registration, or without being exempt, and some knowingly run scams.</p><p>If you deal with a firm (or individual) that is not regulated you may not be covered by the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.financial-ombudsman.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Financial Ombudsman Service</a>&nbsp;or <a href=\"http://www.fscs.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">Financial Services Compensation Scheme</a>&nbsp;if things go wrong. Search for a firm or individual to find out how you are protected.</p><p><b>Protect yourself from scams</b> Find out how to <a href=\"http://www.fca.org.uk/consumers/protect-yourself/unauthorised-firms\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">check you are dealing with a regulated firm</a>.</p><p>You can see <a href=\"http://www.fca.org.uk/consumers/scams/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">what to do if you have been scammed</a>, are concerned about an investment or have been contacted by fraudsters.</p><p>You can also help us protect other people if you <a href=\"http://www.fca.org.uk/consumers/protect-yourself/report-an-unauthorised-firm\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external\">report a scam or unauthorised firm.</a></p>\n                        </div>\n                        \n                    </div>\n                    \n                </div></span>\n            \n           \n            \n \n   </section><div id=\"j_id0:j_id1:j_id103:j_id184\"></div>\n</form>                           \n                        </div> \n                    </div> \n class=\"panel-body\"><p><a href=\"http://www.fca.org.uk/site-info/contact\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external RegisterPanelLink-xx\">Contact the FCA</a> for firm or consumer&nbsp;queries and Register help.</p>\n<a href=\"http://www.bankofengland.co.uk/pages/contact.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"external RegisterPanelLink-xx\">Contact the PRA</a> for prudential queries about banks, building societies, credit unions, insurance firms.<p></p> \n  </div></span> \n                        </div></span>\n                        \n                       \n                        \n Company No. 01920623</span></span>\n                    <script src=\"/resource/1426882958000/ShPo_JQueryTypeAhead/ShPo_JQueryTypeAhead/js/ShPo_SyncSearchBoxes.js\"></script>\n                   \n                    <script>\n                    \n                        \n                        $(document).ready(function() {\n                        \n                        $('#searchBox').typeahead({\n                            minLength: 1,\n                            order: \"asc\",\n                            group: true,\n                            groupMaxItem: 5,\n                            hint: false,\n                            filter: \"lists\", \n                            cache: true,\n                            compression: true,\n                            ttl: 86400000, // 1day\n                            selector: {\n                                filter: \"input-group-btn\",\n                                filterButton: \"btn btn-default\",\n                                dropdown: \"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right\",\n                                list: \"dropdown-menu\",\n                                hint: \"form-control\"\n                            },\n                            source: {\n                                  firms: [\"/ShPo_JsonTypeAheadPage\"],\n                                individuals: [\"/ShPo_JsonTypeAheadContactPage\"]\n                            },\n                            callback: {\n                                onResult: function() {\n                                 $(\"#searchBox\").removeClass(\"loading\");  \n                                },\n                            },\n                            \n                            debug: true\n                        });\n                    });\n                    </script>\n                 </div>\n            </div>\n             \n            \n            \n            <div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"myModalLabel\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"typeofbusinessmodal\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n              <div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n                <div class=\"modal-content\">\n                  <div class=\"modal-header\">\n                    <button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"close\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\"></span></button>\n                    <h3 class=\"modal-title\" id=\"myModalLabel\">Type of business</h3>\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-body\"><p><strong>Financial services firm</strong> - Firms must be authorised to provide regulated products and services, including banking, investments, insurance, mortgages and other financial products and services in the UK. </p><p><strong>Individual</strong> - Individuals (and some firms) must be approved to perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We describe these as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions. </p><p><strong>Payment services firm</strong> - Firms must be authorised or registered to provide payment services, including issuing credit cards and  money transfer operations.</p><p><strong>Consumer Credit Interim</strong> - A consumer credit firm that held an Office of Fair Trading licence and wanted to continue its consumer credit activities had to apply for interim permission. This will last until it has to apply for authorisation or a variation of permission.</p><p><strong>EMoney</strong> - Firms must be authorised or registered to issue electronic money (e-money), which includes pre-paid cards such as travel money cards and some gift cards.</p> <p><strong>Unauthorised firm</strong> - Some firms provide products and services without the required authorisation, or is knowingly running a scam. We strongly suggest you avoid dealing with unauthorised firms.</p><p><strong>Collective investment scheme</strong> - Some collective investment schemes (CIS) are regulated by us, including investment companies with variable capital (open ended investment companies), some unit trusts, and recognised offshore schemes.</p><p><strong>Exempt professional firm</strong> - Some firms (such as solicitors, accountants and chartered surveyors) can perform limited regulated financial activities as part of their normal professional services, without being authorised or an agent of an authorised firm.</p><p><strong>Exchange</strong> - We recognise and supervise certain investment exchanges.</p><p><strong>Not-for-profit body</strong> - Not-for-profit bodies may be covered by a group licence to provide financial services, debt management services and credit information services.</p>&nbsp;\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-footer\">\n                    <button class=\"btn btn-default modalbtn\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\">Close</button>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n           \n            \n            <div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"myModalLabel\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"currentstatusmodal\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n              <div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n                <div class=\"modal-content\">\n                  <div class=\"modal-header\">\n                    <button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"close\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\"></span></button>\n                    <h3 class=\"modal-title\" id=\"myModalLabel\">Current status</h3>\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-body\"><p><strong>Active Individual</strong> - An individual (and some firms) that can perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We describe these individuals and firms as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions.</p> <p><strong>Appointed representative</strong> - A firm or individual that can act on behalf of another firm (its principal) that is authorised in the UK or regulated in another EEA country. The principal is responsible for the appointed representative's activities.</p> <p><strong>Appointed representative  former</strong> - An appointed representative that can no longer provide regulated products and services, but previously could act on behalf of another firm (its principal).</p> <p><strong>Appointed representative  introducer</strong> - A firm that can introduce customers to another firm or members of the firms group, and/or give out certain kinds of marketing material. It must be a representative of a firm authorised by the FCA or PRA, or regulated in the EEA.</p> <p><strong>Approved</strong> - An individual (and some firms) that can perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We describe these individuals and firms as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions.</p><p><strong>Authorised firm</strong> - A firm that is given permission to provide regulated products and services.</p> <p><strong>Authorised firm  applied to cancel</strong> - A firm that has applied to cancel its authorisation but must still meet our standards in dealing with its customers.</p> <p><strong>Authorised firm  in administration</strong> - A firm that has stopped taking on new business but is still authorised and has to continue to meet our standards in dealing with its customers.</p> <p><strong>Authorised firm  in liquidation</strong> - A firm that has stopped taking on new business but is still authorised and has to continue to meet our standards in dealing with its customers.</p> <p><strong>Authorised firm  suspended</strong> - A firm that has to stop providing regulated products and services for a period of time.</p> <p><strong>Authorised electronic money institution</strong> - A firm that we have given permission to issue electronic money (e-money) and provide payment services.</p><p><strong>Authorised payment institution</strong> - A firm that we have given permission to provide payment services.</p> <p><strong>EEA authorised firm</strong> - A firm regulated in another <span class=\"search_popover\" data-toggle=\"popover\" data-placement=\"top\" data-content=\"<div class='searchPopover'> The EEA includes the EU states, plus Iceland, Norway and Liechtenstein.</div>\" data-original-title=\"\" title=\"\">European Economic Area</span> a (EEA) country that can offer certain products or services in the UK. The firm must meet minimum standards agreed across all EEA countries.</p><p><strong>Electronic money agent</strong> - A firm that can issue electronic money (e-money) and provide payment services on behalf of an e-money institution.</p><p><strong>Inactive individual</strong> - An individual (and some firms) that was previously approved to perform certain tasks in a regulated firm. These individuals and firms would have been described as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions. </p><p><strong>No longer authorised firm</strong> - A firm that can no longer provide regulated products and services, but previously was authorised by the PRA and/or FCA. </p><p><strong>Payment services agent</strong> - A firm that can provide payment services on behalf of a payment institution.</p><p><strong>Small electronic money institution</strong> - A firm that can issue electronic money (e-money) and provide payment services. These firms are registered (rather than authorised), which affects how we regulate the firm. </p><p><strong>Small payment institution</strong> - A firm that can provide payment services. These firms are registered (rather than authorised), which affects how we regulate the firm. </p> <p><strong>Unauthorised firm</strong> - Some firms provide products and services without the required authorisation, or is knowingly running a scam. We strongly suggest you avoid dealing with unauthorised firms.</p> <p><strong>No longer Authorised</strong> - This is a firm that can no longer provide regulated products and services, but was previously authorised by the PRA and/or FCA.</p> <p><strong>Cancelled</strong> - The firm has cancelled its interim permission to undertake consumer credit business.</p> <p><strong>Previously IP Registered</strong> - This firm previously had interim permission to perform certain consumer credit activities for the period indicated in this record.  It has since applied for and been authorised to carry out credit activities in its main permission, replacing the interim permission. You should refer to the authorisation record for this firm for the permissions since the interim permission ended.</p> <p><strong>Fully Authorised apart from 2nd charge</strong> - This firm is authorised to run consumer credit business. You should refer to the authorisation information for this firm rather than its interim permission, except for its second charge mortgage business which still comes under its interim permission.</p> <p><strong>Interim Permission Granted</strong> - The firm has interim permission to undertake consumer credit business.</p> <p><strong>IP issued</strong> - The firm has interim permission to undertake consumer credit business.</p> <p><strong>IP provisionally issued</strong> - The firm has interim permission to undertake consumer credit business.</p> <p><strong>IVOP issued</strong> - This firm has interim permission to run consumer credit business and was already authorised to provide financial products and services.</p> <p><strong>IVOP provisionally granted</strong> - The firm has interim permission to undertake consumer credit business and was already authorised to provide financial products and services.</p> <p><strong>Lapsed</strong> - The firm no longer has interim permission to undertake consumer credit business.</p> <p><strong>Revoked</strong> - This firm has had its interim permission to run consumer credit business withdrawn. See the disciplinary and regulatory action section for more information.</p> <p><strong>Suspended</strong> - This firm has had its interim permission to undertake consumer credit business suspended by the FCA and/or PRA. See the Disciplinary and regulatory action about the firm for further information.</p> &nbsp;\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-footer\">\n                    <button class=\"btn btn-default modalbtn\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\">Close</button>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n            \n            \n            \n             \n            <div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"myModalLabel\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"AdvSrchtypeofbusinessmodal\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n              <div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n                <div class=\"modal-content\">\n                  <div class=\"modal-header\">\n                    <button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"close\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\"></span></button>\n                    <h3 class=\"modal-title\" id=\"myModalLabel\">Type of business</h3>\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-body\"><p><strong>Financial services firm</strong> - Firms must be authorised to provide regulated products and services, including banking, investments, insurance, mortgages and other financial products and services in the UK. </p><p><strong>Individual</strong> - Individuals (and some firms) must be approved to perform certain tasks in an authorised firm. We describe these as approved persons and the tasks as controlled functions. </p><p><strong>Collective investment scheme</strong> - Some collective investment schemes (CIS) are regulated by us, including investment companies with variable capital (open ended investment companies), some unit trusts, and recognised offshore schemes.</p>&nbsp;\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-footer\">\n                    <button class=\"btn btn-default modalbtn\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\">Close</button>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n           \n            \n            <div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"myModalLabel\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"AdvSrchcurrentstatusmodal\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n              <div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n                <div class=\"modal-content\">\n                  <div class=\"modal-header\">\n                    <button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"close\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\"></span></button>\n                    <h3 class=\"modal-title\" id=\"myModalLabel\">Current status</h3>\n                  </div>\n                  <div class=\"modal-body\"><p><strong>Authorised firm</strong> - A firm that is given permission to provide regulated products and services.</p><p><strong>Unauthorised firm</strong> - Some firms provide products and services without the required authorisation, or is knowingly running a scam. We strongly suggest you avoid dealing with unauthorised firms.</p><p><strong>Active Individual</strong> - An individual (and some firms) that can perform certain tasks in an authorised firm.
